10#define lgc_h

13#include "lobject.h"
14#include "lstate.h"

16/*
17** Collectable objects may have one of three colors: white, which
18** means the object is not marked; gray, which means the
19** object is marked, but its references may be not marked; and
20** black, which means that the object and all its references are marked.
21** The main invariant of the garbage collector, while marking objects,
22** is that a black object can never point to a white one. Moreover,
23** any gray object must be in a "gray list" (gray, grayagain, weak,
24** allweak, ephemeron) so that it can be visited again before finishing
25** the collection cycle. These lists have no meaning when the invariant
26** is not being enforced (e.g., sweep phase).
27*/
28
29
30
31/* how much to allocate before next GC step */
32#if !defined(GCSTEPSIZE)
33/* ~100 small strings */
34#define GCSTEPSIZE (cast_int(100 * sizeof(TString)))
35#endif
36
37
38/*
39** Possible states of the Garbage Collector
40*/
41#define GCSpropagate 0
42#define GCSatomic 1
43#define GCSswpallgc 2
44#define GCSswpfinobj 3
45#define GCSswptobefnz 4
46#define GCSswpend 5
47#define GCScallfin 6
48#define GCSpause 7
49
50
51#define issweepphase(g) \
52 (GCSswpallgc <= (g)->gcstate && (g)->gcstate <= GCSswpend)
53
54
55/*
56** macro to tell when main invariant (white objects cannot point to black
57** ones) must be kept. During a collection, the sweep
58** phase may break the invariant, as objects turned white may point to
59** still-black objects. The invariant is restored when sweep ends and
60** all objects are white again.
61*/
62
63#define keepinvariant(g) ((g)->gcstate <= GCSatomic)
64
65
66/*
67** some useful bit tricks
68*/
69#define resetbits(x,m) ((x) &= cast(lu_byte, ~(m)))
70#define setbits(x,m) ((x) |= (m))
71#define testbits(x,m) ((x) & (m))
72#define bitmask(b) (1<<(b))
73#define bit2mask(b1,b2) (bitmask(b1) | bitmask(b2))
74#define l_setbit(x,b) setbits(x, bitmask(b))
75#define resetbit(x,b) resetbits(x, bitmask(b))
76#define testbit(x,b) testbits(x, bitmask(b))
77
78
79/* Layout for bit use in 'marked' field: */
80#define WHITE0BIT 0 /* object is white (type 0) */
81#define WHITE1BIT 1 /* object is white (type 1) */
82#define BLACKBIT 2 /* object is black */
83#define FINALIZEDBIT 3 /* object has been marked for finalization */
84/* bit 7 is currently used by tests (luaL_checkmemory) */
85
86#define WHITEBITS bit2mask(WHITE0BIT, WHITE1BIT)
87
88
89#define iswhite(x) testbits((x)->marked, WHITEBITS)
90#define isblack(x) testbit((x)->marked, BLACKBIT)
91#define isgray(x) /* neither white nor black */ \
92 (!testbits((x)->marked, WHITEBITS | bitmask(BLACKBIT)))
93
94#define tofinalize(x) testbit((x)->marked, FINALIZEDBIT)
95
96#define otherwhite(g) ((g)->currentwhite ^ WHITEBITS)
97#define isdeadm(ow,m) (!(((m) ^ WHITEBITS) & (ow)))
98#define isdead(g,v) isdeadm(otherwhite(g), (v)->marked)
99
100#define changewhite(x) ((x)->marked ^= WHITEBITS)
101#define gray2black(x) l_setbit((x)->marked, BLACKBIT)
102
103#define luaC_white(g) cast(lu_byte, (g)->currentwhite & WHITEBITS)
104
105
106/*
107** Does one step of collection when debt becomes positive. 'pre'/'pos'
108** allows some adjustments to be done only when needed. macro
109** 'condchangemem' is used only for heavy tests (forcing a full
110** GC cycle on every opportunity)
111*/
112#define luaC_condGC(L,pre,pos) \
113 { if (G(L)->GCdebt > 0) { pre; luaC_step(L); pos;}; \
114 condchangemem(L,pre,pos); }
115
116/* more often than not, 'pre'/'pos' are empty */
117#define luaC_checkGC(L) luaC_condGC(L,(void)0,(void)0)
118
119
120#define luaC_barrier(L,p,v) ( \
121 (iscollectable(v) && isblack(p) && iswhite(gcvalue(v))) ? \
122 luaC_barrier_(L,obj2gco(p),gcvalue(v)) : cast_void(0))
123
124#define luaC_barrierback(L,p,v) ( \
125 (iscollectable(v) && isblack(p) && iswhite(gcvalue(v))) ? \
126 luaC_barrierback_(L,p) : cast_void(0))
127
128#define luaC_objbarrier(L,p,o) ( \
129 (isblack(p) && iswhite(o)) ? \
130 luaC_barrier_(L,obj2gco(p),obj2gco(o)) : cast_void(0))
131
132#define luaC_upvalbarrier(L,uv) ( \
133 (iscollectable((uv)->v) && !upisopen(uv)) ? \
134 luaC_upvalbarrier_(L,uv) : cast_void(0))
